data.description: Rare 2 detached dwellings on one lot! Perfect for multi-generational living or simply live-in and rent the other half, generating a good source of rental income. Great functional floor plan: main house built in '71 has 3-bdrm/1.5-bath and the lower level has a recreational room with a 1-bdrm and a 1 full bath, total living space is 1,544 sqft. Cottage built in '68 consist of 2-bdrm and 1 full bath, total living space is 500 sqft. Main house has upgraded kitchen, vinyl wood planks, interior painting and the lower level offers a potential to add your personal upgrades.  Plenty of open parking spaces, this lot can accommodate up to 4 parking on rear side of Mapu Ln. and 1 parking on the front side on Ihe St. The dwellings have separate electric meters and share one water/sewer meter. Located in short distances to freeway access, bus-lines, highly ranked schools, medical centers, lots of local eateries, downtown Honolulu, historic Chinatown and many more essentials of the culturally rich Liliha neighborhood. A photo has been virtually staged (enhanced).
